,Recommended,266490,15390199,"Posted: 15 April, 2015",all,Uriyeah55,"Well, time to give it my own review!Sincerely I’m not sure about how to start. Lili: Child of Geos is simple. Wonderfully beatiful but simple. It’s a short adventure that only enters by the eyes. I think the best way to structure this review is with the classical order: Graphics, Gameplay, etcccccccccc.GraphicsAlready clear, right? They are astonishing. If you can play the game at it’s fullest you will enjoy more than I can express. I remember taking an insane amount of screenshots because I just loved everything so hard. The environtments are very well done too, I could feel like I wouldn’t mind to live when the game happens (yep, I know that sounds cringy but come on).PlotDoesn’t shine much. You’re the teacher’s daughter going into a mysterious island to gather rare flowers. You find weirdos that can talk and are cursed and you don’t even ask why. It’s like the game itself is rolling and saying come on just play you don’t need a history behind everything, right?GameplayIt isn’t bad, but repetitive. Run, gather flower, run, kick jar, “fight” enemy. Repeat x999. There are no real combats in the game so it’s perfect for a child (and for 20+ years old weirdos like myself huehue). Lili: Child of Geos forces you to grind a lot. To defeat a lot of enemies is the main task of the game, because rarely you find puzzles that need some kind of “research” to success (more like talking to the NPC that helps you every single time).If going straight to the point, the game is extremely short. And that’s the main reason because I don’t recommend buying it at full price.LacksWell, it depends of the target of the game. The main character, Lili, only can say things like “Hi” or “Oh” and has only a few animations. As the game is an indie itself I won’t blame that, because I’m sure the company spend most of the time in developing the wonderful environtment.AchievementsI’m a sick lover of achievements, and although I got them all in this one. I’m gonna blame that. Most of them are grinding at it’s finest: scare 500 birds, break 1000 jars, etc. Just an excuse to play some time more, and that’s a very negative point. But whatever, they had to supply the lack of content.OverallAmazing environment and atmosphere. Perfect for kids with the non-violence and there’s no hurry to finish the game. Also has a lot of references to other games and if the player is not a kid will get most of them. Consider to buy when at sale."
