,Recommended,266490,13838716,"Posted: 4 January, 2015",all,Kelocena,"My boyfriend and I played this game together and greatly enjoyed it (overall).Overall rating: 8/10Objectionable Content: Mild? (bordering on 'some'?). There is some ""humor"" that is questionable both in taste and apropriateness for younger audiences. *See end of review for details, including trigger warnings and warnings for parents.As far as the rest of the game goes, the atmosphere and evironments are absolutely stunning and worthy of screenshots. and the music is varied and well-suited. There is a bit of a Zelda-esque atmosphere which comes as no surprising seeing all the little Zelda references sprinkled throughout the game. It was refreshing to play a game that was not violent, yet still involved ""beating the bad guys."" So many of the characters you meet are adorable and hilarious, and have succeeded in getting laughs out of both of us. It is worth talking to all of them; they say some of the most ridiculous things. The gameplay centered around a very simple concept: pick flowers, though it was a pleasant surprise to find that it could be still be challenging sometimes. I would easily recommend this game to most of my friends.Pros:+ Fun, non-violent gameplay+ Gorgeous visuals+ World worth exploring (not overwhelming like big sandbox games)+ NPCs worth interacting with+ Nice soundtrackCons:- The aforementioned tasteless jokes (why it is 8/10 and not 10/10. they were pretty gross.)- Unexpected spike in difficulty between areas/levels.- Does not clearly state its save mechanism (it's autosave, btw) and does not indicate what triggers a save- Bit pricey for the length. I wouldn't pay more than ~$12.- No replay value (one achievement needs ~half a 2nd playthrough but that's it.)*There are a small handful of instances in which sexual harassment is normalized or made into a joke. Fortunately, they are few and far between, and most are easy enough to ignore and move past, but I can see a couple of the jokes being potentially triggering - especially since you would not see it coming from a game like this (we were very surprised ourselves). None of these jokes are a big piece of the game, but it's enough to make it not an 100% all-ages friendly game. To be more specific,TRIGGER & PARENT WARNING: Stalking (creepy photos of Lili and her butt in one NPC's place), Sexual harassment (abuse of power/authority), Sexual abuse (1 joke)."
