,Recommended,266490,19279292,"Posted: 25 November, 2015",all,White Sheep,"I finished the game in less than 7 hours. It is an RPG style game with beautiful graphics. The main character Lili is sent to an island to collect flowers. There are two types of habitants on the island - spirits who carry flowers and constructs who serves spirits. Lili then joins the movement to topple the powerful spirit-led government and free the constructs.The battle mechanics is simple, click and drag flowers off the spirit's back. It is a nice and child-friendly way to present an RPG, while it isn't too boring for older people. For me, the RPG adventure and graphics is the selling point of this game.Unless you are obsessed with getting 100% achievement, replayability is low. According to the $1/hour rule, this game is a recommend at around $6."
,Recommended,266490,18969734,"Posted: 9 November, 2015",all,Encephalon,"Lili: Child of Geos is a very short indie action adventure game featuring a schoolgirl Lili and her whimsical adventures on a strange land called Geos.This was originally released as an iOS game and it shows. The game can be completed within about 3 hours. It isn't a very complicated game and is extremely kid-friendly. The whole game tasks you to explore around the land while doing simple subquests for its inhabitants.There are some hostile enemies called ""Spirits"" that you will encounter, but because this game is kid-friendly, you don't actually engage in combat per se. The way to defeat these Spirits is to pluck flowers from them. Yes it sounds kindda silly, but then again, this is a cute little silly game in a way.The graphics looks gorgeous despite it being an iOS game and the artstyle looks somewhat like Legend of Zelda: Wind Waker although the bloom effect is used abit too much. Soundtrack is appropriately cute with little jingles and the animations are pretty well done.The over-arching story while simple and humorous can be unexpectedly dark for an older audience with its underlying story of slavery and freedom. Younger children will however probably be too distracted by the action to focus on the story.The game also features lots of in-jokes and item collections that pays homage to classic games. (Eg: Super Mario, Legend of Zelda, Portal 2 etc.) It can be quite addictive to try to collect everything and the game allows you to continue to play even if you have completed the main story.Overall Rating: 7.0 / 10A very short family friendly game that is surprisingly quite entertaining. While the game is probably targeted at children, there are some interesting treat for older audiences. Still, with gameplay at a very short 3 hours, i'd recommend only to buy when on a sale."
